article.headline: UNLV 95, Canisius 70
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Mike Moser had 19 points and nine rebounds to lead five players scoring in double figures in UNLV's 95-70 victory against Canisius on Thursday. The Rebels (3-0) shot 61 percent (33 for 54) and made 55 percent (11 for 20) from 3-point range. Oscar Bellfield added 14 points and 10 assists, Justin Hawkins 14 points and five steals and Chace Stanback and Carlos Lopez 10 points each. Alshwan Hymes had 16 points for the Golden Griffiths (1-2). The Rebels led 54-33 at halftime as UNLV outscored Canisius 22-10 to finish the first half.
